<br>
However, what I've seen is that the mobs wander a lot, have a large agro range, and aren't tightly bunched together.  I know that we typically like to have a bard pulling for their tracking skill and speed in bringing back mobs from great distances, as well as their ability to kite adds around until the groups can deal with them.<br>
<br>
Seems like this wouldn't be a very good place for duoing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=variathemage>Varia the mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 11:26:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG</span><hr size=1> I used to hunt a lot in Growth in the form of a raid the first two months of Velious.  I don't know if the zone has been changed any other than hearing the queen bitch (Tunare.  yes, I'm an inky <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) is a good bit easier than she was at first.<br>
<br>
The goat people someone mentioned are known as protectors of growth.  They spawn at a set interval.  My guess is every 30 minutes, but it has been too long for me to know for sure.  They have a set spawn point.  If anyone KoS is in the zone, they come charging for you no matter where you are.  They spawn two at a time.  They seemed fairly resistant to magic, not sure about othere resists (was using shock of steel at the time).  What makes them a total pain is they build their agro the entire time they are running towards you.  That means your clerics are building huge agro with their CHs.  The way we worked around that was our clerics would keep up both divine aura and divine barrier, then use them as they needed till the tanks could draw their attention.  They didn't seem to hit harder than the average mob in Growth.  No idea on their hit points.<br>
<br>
I don't recommend trying this as your listed levels.  I think you would die repeatedly. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108671">Varia Darselai</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khysanth>Khysanth</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#333333>(12/4/02 6:25:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hmmm</span><hr size=1> Last I knew on our previous Tunare raid, PoGs were broken and not spawning...this is on $tormhammer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=klymaxusstarym>Klymaxus Starym</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(12/15/02 6:26:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> they don't have the PoGs anymore in the zone. i have been soloing in PoG for awhile now. i have epic and 60 just need to nuke/heal till mob is dead. pulling is not bad at all also. just pull to the lake and your fine. <p><!--EZCODE IMAG